outputs.output_descr:
Project Initiation Plan (PIP) is developed with twin objectives of undertaking key and immediate interventions that lay foundations for long term peace and stability in the country in the form of developing a credible infrastructure for peace. The project duration is November 2012 to December 2013.
Secondly, PIP also is intended to develop a full project document incorporating the experiences of the initiation phase and consolidating the entry-points that have been created. 
Following are key outputs: 
Non-State Dialogue Component
1.	Mediation, dialogue and negotiation mechanisms developed at national levels;
2.	Capacity building for members of the National Elders Forum in design and process aspects of dialogue and mediation provided;
3.	Independent Secretariat fully functional and research support for evidence based analysis to the National Elders Forum provided;
Political Parties Dialogue Component 
1.	Skills and capacities for internal dialogue and political settlements amongst members of National Consultative Forum strengthened;
Local Peace-building component
1.	Strengthened local conflict management capacities in specific regions.
